    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yes it should be readable, it seems from the people I follow that are doing a lot of CSS that postprocessors are the way to go for modern CSS stacks.\n\nThey are the babel of CSS: write real CSS using latest CSS specs and compile to CSS.\n\nSo you won't have to re-learn CSS when new CSS features are released to browsers, you already know them.\n\nI agree it can be a shift from being good at SASS.\n",
